Ing '''pH''' sukad ne ning panga-asidu (kaslam) o panga-[[Base (chemistry)|alkaline]] ning metung a solusiun. Deng solusiun king danum o aqueous solutions king pali o temperaturang 25&nbsp;°C a maki pH a kulang king pitu (7.0) tuturing da lang asidu, kabang alkaline o basic no man detang maki pH a maigit king pitu. Nung saktu yang 7.0 ing kayang pH, tuturing deng 'neutral' king temperaturang 25&nbsp;°C uling king temperaturang ita, pante ya ing bilang da reng [[hydronium ion|H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>]] karetang [[hydroxide|OH<sup>−</sup>]] king purung danum. Magdependi ya ing pH king [[Activity (chemistry)|aktibidad]] da reng [[hydronium]] [[ion]] (H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>),<ref>[http://www.jp.horiba.com/story_e/ph/ph01_03.htm HORIBA : The story of pH<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> dapot kareng maina (o dilute) a solusiun, malyari yang gamitan ing [[Concentration#molarity|molarity]] ning H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> a e midadayu ketang ustung kuenta <ref>[http://chem.lapeer.org/Chem2Docs/pHFacts.html pH Facts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Ing (H<sup>+</sup> pane deng gagamitan a katumbas ning H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>.) Uling magdependi ya ing pH king aktibidad da reng ion, metung a kaurian (property) a e malaguang sukdan o karkulan ibat king teoria (theoretically), masakit yang pakibaluan ing eksaktung sukad ning pH ning metung a solusiun. keraklan, makukua ya ing sukad ning metung a solusiun kapamilata'ning pamiyanti (comparing) kareng solusiun a e ra pa balu pH karetang balu ra na pH, at ating [[#Measurement|mapilan a paralan]] bang marapat iti.

Ing minunang migpakilala king konseptu ning pH ya pin ing chemist ibat [[Denmark]] a i [[S. P. L. Sørensen]] king [[Carlsberg Laboratory]]<ref>Carlsberg Research Centre history page, http://www.crc.dk/history.shtml</ref> in [[1909]]. Dakal la reng sasabian dang penibatan ning lagyung pH, kayabe no reng ''pondus hydrogenii'', ''potentia hydrogenii'' ([[Latin]]),<ref name="madscipost">[http://www.madsci.org/posts/archives/sep2001/1000136604.Sh.r.html Re: What does pH stand for and who invented it? Can you help me?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''potentiel hydrogène'' ([[French language|French]]), ampong ''potential of hydrogen'' ([[English language|English]]).<ref>[http://www.morrisonlabs.com/ph_study_guide.htm pH study guide<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

